OL,3,CCouncil 'disappointed' after building
OL,4,Cowner pulls out of asylum-seeker deal
OL,6,FRoger Gough, Leader of Kent County
OL,7,FCouncil (KCC), said: "It is
OL,8,Fdisappointing to have to confirm that
OL,9,FOcean Heights on the Isle of Sheppey
OL,10,Fhas been withdrawn from sale.
OL,12,F"The building was one of seven
OL,13,Fadditional facilities we identified to
OL,14,Fsupplement the two existing reception
OL,15,Fcentres for unaccompanied asylum-
OL,16,Fseeking (UAS) children. These
OL,17,Fbuildings, funded by central
OL,18,Fgovernment, will increase our capacity
OL,19,Fto accommodate and care for all UAS
OL,20,Fchildren arriving in Kent, as required
OL,21,Fby the High Court.
